<subSubSection id="EF7491434DCCA7473E5152DA7328D2F1" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="species composition">
<paragraph id="8D4F239F943CE63D8299C0D312C39DB7" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Species composition.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2BFD3E3D8F223FEE56D2CDAB001FEB59" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
There are at least 14 valid species in the Western Palearctic: 
<taxonomicName id="75C46D90BD4DF59BAB448EE76E340C76" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Megachile) alpicola" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alpicola" subGenus="Megachile">Megachile alpicola</taxonomicName>
Alfken, 1924, 
<taxonomicName id="0E39E9852CF05232C47DF702624178E0" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) armenia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armenia" subGenus="M.">M. armenia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="D40FABA939F2F0BC21164B4D90561DA0" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) bombycina" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombycina" subGenus="M.">M. bombycina</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2BEA40D370F0388465948452E9743F0F" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) calloleuca" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calloleuca" subGenus="M.">M. calloleuca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="17E0C0F6DF90BBCB71D0D32D72865281" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) centuncularis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centuncularis" subGenus="M.">M. centuncularis</taxonomicName>
(Linnaeus, 1758), 
<taxonomicName id="DC20EF32DCFB9AB5D005C16A57A2C860" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) genalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genalis" subGenus="M.">M. genalis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="073DA0284C4ECCA5D8069BB751BB8946" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) lapponica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lapponica" subGenus="M.">M. lapponica</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="31217190DBDC0B30398F924A41B44124" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) ligniseca" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ligniseca" subGenus="M.">M. ligniseca</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03A11E1804685989E0C73A1C23D0D362" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) melanopyga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopyga" subGenus="M.">M. melanopyga</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5FB4F884CB2F637667D659D7BE919308" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) melanota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanota" subGenus="M.">M. melanota</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="3E9C8D370D5AB4849A7B82DF0F47A5D1" originalValue="Pérez">Perez</normalizedToken>
, 1895, 
<taxonomicName id="B252591189E72EC588B12D97AFF619F0" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) octosignata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octosignata" subGenus="M.">M. octosignata</taxonomicName>
Nylander, 1852, 
<taxonomicName id="CBF5081C3F97DA4741FA8C62BC16D9F3" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pilicrus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilicrus" subGenus="M.">M. pilicrus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CDBCF1122D586552A20C9A71802FC31F" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pyrenaea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrenaea" subGenus="M.">M. pyrenaea</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="FF32A89DC1F7BAC36B2BF32EED0999F1" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) versicolor" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor" subGenus="M.">M. versicolor</taxonomicName>
. I have not been able to locate the type of 
<taxonomicName id="9FBF9118177F7A8303D976062BC4D892" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) dacica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dacica" subGenus="M.">M. dacica</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="BA88C6507193AFBE10A25FA7261056DA" originalValue="Mocsáry">Mocsary</normalizedToken>
, 1879; 
<bibRefCitation id="06B7A84A85A33C96664520F3D00D3617" author="Schwarz, M" journalOrPublisher="Entomofauna Supplement 8, Ansfelden" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" title="Katalog der Bienen Oesterreichs, Deutschlands und der Schweiz (Hymenoptera, Apidae)." year="1996">Schwarz et al. (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="8A01DBFD14C41F9C4C95BC8F4E5D93E0" author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Eucera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="3 - 18" title="Bienen (Hymenoptera, Apidae) als Bluetenbesucher von Odontitesviscosus und Odontitesluteus (Scrophulariaceae)." url="http://www.wildbienen.info/downloads/eucera-6–2011.pdf" volume="6" year="2011">Westrich (2011)</bibRefCitation>
recognized this species as valid; in contrast, according to identified material in his collection (OLML), B. 
<normalizedToken id="0B98F72FFF5C5F16E4C7D6DDA767B1CB" originalValue="Tkalců">Tkalcu</normalizedToken>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="ECA295E649B64CF9DCE60388B44B184B" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae dacica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dacica">dacica</taxonomicName>
as a valid subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="BC4C9223329726DABD67D013B7C35778" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) lapponica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lapponica" subGenus="M.">M. lapponica</taxonomicName>
. The status of 
<taxonomicName id="FD351BCE0C6C08F1D8B5D00C214CADD6" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) melanota" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanota" subGenus="M.">M. melanota</taxonomicName>
is unclear, as it may represent a dark color form of 
<taxonomicName id="6683150C7490E8002EEF245638C6AB21" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) octosignata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octosignata" subGenus="M.">M. octosignata</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F7D23CBC1D13816748DAF10FC104347A" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="5293D2A5DD57118178180E88E00DB508" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D53129BC92144C661EA6F80DA1DD93E" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
All species are leafcutters and build brood cells made of leaf fragments (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="B762110976F86B8CEFC6D7E4E8CC1A04" author="Malysheva, MS" journalOrPublisher="Entomological review" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="268 - 276" title="Leaf-cutting bees of the genus Megachile Latr. (Hymenoptera, Megachilidae) injurious to young forest stands and shelter belts in the USSR." volume="37" year="1958">Malysheva 1958</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9A6591518EF56CB26479441F2F9FA0FC" author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="9BCBCC3484F4E9E961A2C85AD85200C6" author="Ruhnke, H" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Gesellschaft fuer Allgemeine und Angewandte Entomologie" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="513 - 516" title="Zur Nistbiologie der Megachilegenalis Mor (Hymenoptera: Apidae)." volume="12" year="2000">Ruhnke 2000</bibRefCitation>
); no Palearctic species appears to use petals as documented in the Nearctic 
<taxonomicName id="C48DF0267944583377E90221222FC1E1" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Megachile) montivaga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montivaga" subGenus="Megachile">Megachile montivaga</taxonomicName>
(Michener, 2007, and references therein; 
<bibRefCitation id="2EDD484E52F096483FDB5E8ADD3FFF43" author="Orr, MC" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Melittology" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="1 - 6" title="Megachile (Megachile) montivaga (Hymenoptera: Megachilidae) nesting in live thistle (Asteraceae: Cirsium)." url="https://doi.org/10.17161/jom.v0i48.4847" volume="48" year="2015">Orr et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
). The nests are mostly located in existing, above-ground cavities; some species such as 
<taxonomicName id="96149C7195C03067D4DCB5360907ABB9" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) centuncularis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centuncularis" subGenus="M.">M. centuncularis</taxonomicName>
are flexible and nest both in above-ground cavities and in the soil (
<bibRefCitation id="23763323219778A959DE4479198B27F0" author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
, and references therein). Nests of 
<taxonomicName id="99F38D3A0ACCB777EB685133579857E2" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pyrenaea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyrenaea" subGenus="M.">M. pyrenaea</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="5688E2BFBC3BF8578BC96068AD368905" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) octosignata" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="octosignata" subGenus="M.">M. octosignata</taxonomicName>
are placed under stones or in the soil (
<bibRefCitation id="B7BF179125445EBBB540893CB948658B" author="Ferton, C" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="401 - 422" title="Notes detachees sur l'instinct des hymenopteres melliferes et ravisseurs (5 eme serie) avec la description d'une espece nouvelle." volume="78" year="1909">Ferton 1909</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="44821B451D718A19290557BC73D197BC" author="Grandi, G" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino dell'Istituto di Entomologia dell'Universita di Bologna" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" title="Studi di un entomologo sugli imenotteri superiori" volume="25" year="1961">Grandi 1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F0309022229D294B8817F1A78A3E8405" author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
), and a nest of 
<taxonomicName id="593C744351806FEA7AAEE952C256BA34" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) melanopyga" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopyga" subGenus="M.">M. melanopyga</taxonomicName>
was found &quot;loose in the grass&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="08B307553BB69FC1827BE7BFFD866F66" author="Friese, H" journalOrPublisher="Friedlaender, Berlin" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" title="Die Bienen Europa's (Apidae europaeae). Theil V. Solitaere Apiden: Genus Lithurgus. Genus Megachile (Chalicodoma)." year="1898">Friese 1898</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="1428DC7D043F0CD5EA4124DAA265F64F" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) genalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genalis" subGenus="M.">M. genalis</taxonomicName>
exclusively nests in standing stems, favoring fresh stems, thus from plants of the same year; the female digs an opening and places the brood cells vertically above or below the entrance (
<bibRefCitation id="745875B1F68ACCF8C37D227F636E7466" author="Ruhnke, H" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Gesellschaft fuer Allgemeine und Angewandte Entomologie" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="513 - 516" title="Zur Nistbiologie der Megachilegenalis Mor (Hymenoptera: Apidae)." volume="12" year="2000">Ruhnke 2000</bibRefCitation>
, and references therein). According to a brief account by 
<bibRefCitation id="0CA98B1668D5FE78E5CCF75DB550BC04" author="Friese, H" journalOrPublisher="Friedlaender, Berlin" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" title="Die Bienen Europa's (Apidae europaeae). Theil V. Solitaere Apiden: Genus Lithurgus. Genus Megachile (Chalicodoma)." year="1898">Friese (1898)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BE8BA5374E44E5E4271C1395565B7925" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pilicrus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilicrus" subGenus="M.">M. pilicrus</taxonomicName>
nests in dry stems of thistles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C0296304657CE5CBD3ECF7AE3C498D1F" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Most species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="2693978138BB2CAD5C0DE31CCD247C14" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Megachile)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Megachile">Megachile</taxonomicName>
are polylectic, often with a preference for 
<taxonomicName id="1C81D55E11AC62ABF8A56DE0C637B085" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Fabaceae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6E72AFE9595852DD83EFC310B695171C" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="95ADDB1604F1694B65CFF7B4A12E81BD" author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="CC2DBD2A3B28B6C513ABB099DFC511B0" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Megachile) lapponica" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lapponica" subGenus="Megachile">Megachile lapponica</taxonomicName>
is an oligolege on 
<taxonomicName id="6FC7E9461C5F5376B01F3114976F2145" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Onagraceae" genus="Epilobium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Epilobium" order="Myrtales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Epilobium</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FE5588B6E617B88726C4C29DE82A6215" author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C34BF9BBD45DC793B9BEC4A91F65CB3D" author="Kuehn, J" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen der Deutschen Gesellschaft fuer Allgemeine und Angewandte Entomologie" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="389 - 392" title="Ressourcenaufteilung zwischen der oligolektischen Blattschneiderbiene Megachilelapponica L. (Hymenoptera, Apiformes) und anderen Bluetenbesuchern am schmalblaettrigen Weidenroeschen (Epilobiumangustifolium, Onagraceae)." volume="15" year="2006">
<normalizedToken id="E6224CA08331294ACDD91560649096A9" originalValue="Kühn">Kuehn</normalizedToken>
et al. 2006
</bibRefCitation>
), while 
<taxonomicName id="D82C8AE95465D0017F914AF97AAB54C2" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) genalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genalis" subGenus="M.">M. genalis</taxonomicName>
is possibly oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName id="22EE25910DA14BDEFCA1BBD7D5B7810C" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Asteraceae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D3CD62A66B77874CC9571B87BCC414C6" author="Westrich, P" journalOrPublisher="Ulmer, Stuttgart" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" title="Die Wildbienen Baden-Wuerttembergs." year="1989">Westrich 1989</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="97D44446C2B2565026502EB5FB63A7F1" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (M.) pilicrus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilicrus" subGenus="M.">M. pilicrus</taxonomicName>
is oligolectic on 
<taxonomicName id="1B75BF3DFEEA396DFE32C61B3845C9C1" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subfamily" subfamily="Carduoideae">Carduoideae</taxonomicName>
and its hind trochanter and femur are covered by modified, stiff hairs, as observed in some 
<taxonomicName id="2C574A63FF5DEEA4C93CA74546ABCC47" authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Carduoideae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Carduoideae (Eutricharaea)" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Eutricharaea">Eutricharaea</taxonomicName>
species specialized on these plants (
<bibRefCitation id="4783AA55030CBF68F959FB8A850488DC" author="Mueller, A" journalOrPublisher="Apidologie" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="329 - 337" title="A specialized pollen-harvesting device in western palaearctic bees of the genus Megachile (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Megachilidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1051/apido:2004020" volume="35" year="2004">
<normalizedToken id="7B7F1B09668BDFFBDC2B824DE77A855B" originalValue="Müller">Mueller</normalizedToken>
and Bansac 2004
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
